# Puff — client build configuration.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values, then build or run with:
#
#   flutter run   --dart-define-from-file=.env
#   flutter build apk --dart-define-from-file=.env      # or ipa / appbundle / …
#
# These values are compiled into the app at build time (they back the
# `String.fromEnvironment(...)` reads in lib/main.dart). That is expected and
# safe: the anon / publishable key is a PUBLIC client credential — it only
# grants what Row-Level Security allows, which for an untrusted caller is
# nothing. The real security boundary is RLS plus the edge functions, never
# the secrecy of this key.
#
# NEVER put a server secret here. The `service_role` key bypasses RLS and must
# only live in Supabase (dashboard secrets / `supabase secrets set`), never in
# a client build. If a value can bypass RLS, it does not belong in this file.
#
# Both values may be left empty: the app then runs 100% on-device. The entire
# free tier needs no cloud, and Pro / sync flows degrade to "try again online".

# Base URL of your Supabase project — the host the edge functions live under.
#   Local (device / iOS sim):  http://localhost:54321
#   Local (Android emulator):  http://10.0.2.2:54321   (localhost is the emulator itself)
#   Hosted:                    https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
PUFF_SUPABASE_URL=

# Publishable "anon" key for the project above. Public by design (see note).
#   Local:   printed as "anon key" by `supabase start`
#   Hosted:  Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project API keys → anon / public
PUFF_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
